  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Document Controller",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description &amp; Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Control incoming and outgoing project records in accordance with established procedures</li>\n  <li>Duplicate and distribute documents</li>\n  <li>Facilitate timely document review, approval and documentation in an effective and efficient manner</li>\n  <li>Control all aspects of documentation throughout project's life cycle including:</li>\n  <li>Catalogue, post, distribute, track and compile hard and softcopy documents at all project stages</li>\n  <li>Assist project team by coordinating document status and distribution</li>\n  <li>Audit documents to ensure that project files are current and all stakeholders are adopting the prescribed documentation protocol</li>\n  <li>Ensure Project Documental Control policies and procedures to assist in maintaining a current and organized project document management system</li>\n  <li>Provide support for change control and document control processes for the project</li>\n  <li>Track all documents correspondences and transactions</li>\n  <li>file and archive documentation to facilitate easy retrieval</li>\n  <li>Assist completion of requests, searches and queries</li>\n  <li>Prepare and handover all final as-built documentation</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Criteria:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum O levels certificate or equivalent</li>\n  <li>at least 5 years of relevant working experience in registry and document management</li>\n  <li>Good document control skills; knowledge on ISO 9001 standards will be preferred</li>\n  <li>Good working knowledge of MS Office and adept at spreadsheets and file management systems</li>\n  <li>Prior experience with Project Information Management and Electronic Document Management Systems (EDMS)</li>\n  <li>Working hours: Monday - Friday, 8:30am - 6pm</li>\n</ul>",
